'''Jyotiranjan Srichandan Ray''' (born 1970) is an Indian geochemist, geochronologist and a professor at the [[Physical Research Laboratory]].<ref name="Ray, Mohanty get coveted award">{{Cite web |url=http://www.orissapost.com/ray-mohanty-get-coveted-award/ |title=Ray, Mohanty get coveted award |date=September 30, 2015 |publisher=Orissa Post}}</ref> He is known for his studies on the [[geochronology]] of the Indian subcontinent<ref name="Volcano becomes a natural laboratory">{{Cite web |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/indiahome/indianews/article-2306558/QUANTUM-LEAP-Trade-deal-EU-trip-patent-law.html |title=Volcano becomes a natural laboratory |date=April 10, 2013 |publisher=Daily Mall}}</ref> and his studies have been documented in several peer-reviewed articles;<ref name="Jyotiranjan S Ray">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ias.ac.in/listing/bibliography/jess/Jyotiranjan_S._Ray |title=Jyotiranjan S Ray |date=2016 |publisher=Indian Academy of Sciences|work=List of publications}}</ref>{{Refn|group=note|Please see ''Selected bibliography'' section}} [[ResearchGate]] and [[Google Scholar]], online repositories of scientific articles, have listed 53<ref name="On ResearchGate">{{Cite web |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Jyotiranjan_Ray |title=On ResearchGate |date=2016 |publisher=ResearchGate}}</ref> and 59 of them respectively.<ref name="On Google Scholar">{{Cite web |url=https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=6jCEVJQAAAAJ&hl=en |title=On Google Scholar |date=2016 |publisher=Google Scholar}}</ref> He has authored a book, ''Vindhyan Geology: Status and Perspectives'', published in 2006 by the Indian Academy of Sciences<ref name="Ray2006">{{cite book|author=Jyotiranjan S. Ray|title=Vindhyan Geology: Status and Perspectives|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kzPGPgAACAAJ|year=2006|publisher=Indian Acad. of Sciences}}</ref> and has also contributed chapters to books published by others.<ref name="RaySen2010">{{cite book|author1=Jyotisankar Ray|author2=Gautam Sen|author3=Biswajit Ghosh|title=Topics in Igneous Petrology|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Obw5jLeDbd0C&pg=PA161|date=6 December 2010|publisher=Springer Science & Business Media|isbn=978-90-481-9600-5|pages=161–}}</ref><ref name="Kale2014">{{cite book|author=Vishwas S. Kale|author2=Jyotiranjan S. Ray |title=Landscapes and Landforms of India|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=t_MsBAAAQBAJ&pg=PR12|date=23 May 2014|publisher=Springer|isbn=978-94-017-8029-2|pages=12–}}</ref>

Ray, born on 16 July 1970,<ref name="Brief Profile of the Awardee">{{Cite web |url=http://ssbprize.gov.in/Content/Detail.aspx?AID=514 |title=Brief Profile of the Awardee |date=2016 |publisher=Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize |access-date=November 12, 2016}}</ref> in the Indian state of [[Odisha]],<ref name="Odisha CM felicitated scientists Jyotiranjan Srichandan, Dr. Bedangadas Mohanty">{{Cite web |url=http://m.orissadiary.com/article.asp?.src=hd.62092 |title=Odisha CM felicitated scientists Jyotiranjan Srichandan, Dr. Bedangadas Mohanty |date= October 10, 2015 |publisher=Orissa Diary}}</ref> is a recipient of several honors including Best Ph.D. Thesis Award of the Physical Research Laboratory, Young Associateship of the [[Indian Academy of Sciences]], Young Scientist Medal of the [[Indian National Science Academy]], [[Krishnan Medal]] of the [[Indian Geophysical Union]],<ref name="Krishnan Medal">{{Cite web |url=http://www.igu.in/awards.htm |title=Krishnan Medal |date=2016 |publisher=Indian Geophysical Union}}</ref> National Geoscience Award of the [[Ministry of Mines (India)|Ministry of Mines]]<ref name="National Geoscience Award">{{Cite web |url=http://www.mines.nic.in/writereaddata/Content/A_NationalGeoscience_Awardees1995-2012.pdf |title=National Geoscience Award |date=2016 |publisher=Ministry of Mines (India) |page=55}}</ref> and Physical Research Laboratory Research Award.<ref name="Faculty profile">{{Cite web |url=https://www.prl.res.in/~jsray/ |title=Faculty profile |date=2016 |publisher=Physical Research Laboratory}}</ref> The [[Council of Scientific and Industrial Research]], the apex agency of the Government of India for scientific research, awarded him the [[Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize for Science and Technology]], one of the highest Indian science awards for his contributions to Sweta, Atmosphere, Ocean and Planetary Sciences in 2015.<ref name="View Bhatnagar Awardees">{{cite web | url=http://ssbprize.gov.in/Content/AwardeeList.aspx | title=View Bhatnagar Awardees | publisher=Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize | date=2016 | accessdate=November 12, 2016}}</ref>{{Refn|group=note|Long link - please select award year to see details}}

