'''Karel Čáslavský''' (28 January 1937 – 2 January 2013) was a [[Czech Republic|Czech]] [[film historian]] and [[television host]]. Čáslavský worked as a historian for the National Film Archive (Národní filmový archiv) of the [[Czech Republic]] (and [[Czechoslovakia]]) from 1963 until his death in 2013.<ref name=rp>{{cite news|first=|last=|title=Film historian Karel Čáslavský dies aged 75 |url=http://www.radio.cz/en/section/news/news-2013-01-02 |work=[[Radio Prague]] |publisher= |date=2013-01-02 |accessdate=2013-01-03}}</ref>
Čáslavský created and hosted several [[television show]]s including the long-running ''In Search of Lost Time'', which aired on [[Czech TV]] for more than twenty years.<ref name=rp/> In the series, ''In Search of Lost Time'', Čáslavský presented, discussed and aired archival films.<ref name=rp/> Čáslavský also authored a two volume [[biography]] series on Czech and Czechoslovak film actors.<ref name=rp/>
Čáslavský died in [[Prague]] on 2 January 2013, at the age of 75.<ref name=rp/>
