The '''Kenyon Medal''' is awarded every two years by the [[British Academy]] 'in recognition of work in the field of [[classical studies]] and [[archaeology]]'. The medal was [[endowed]] by [[Frederic G. Kenyon|Sir Frederic Kenyon]] and was first awarded in 1957.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kenyon Medal for Classical Studies and Archaeology|url=http://www.britac.ac.uk/about/medals/kenyon.cfm|website=Prizes and medals|publisher=British Academy|accessdate=13 June 2015}}</ref>
